{"key":"processedPost-10842470","value":{"id":10842470,"first":10842238,"last":10842470,"when":1250048391,"utime":"08/12/09 06:39 AM","cleanedPost":"The rye won't EVER germinate if you follow the tek and rinse in hot tap water.&nbsp; <br />Soaking less than four hours can lead to burst kernels when you boil or PC because too much water is absorbed in too short a time.&nbsp; Over 24 hours soaking and the bacterial endospores that have germinated will have made a few billion new endospores, defeating the purpose since at least some of them will survive the PC.&nbsp; Long soak times actually lead to more contamination, not less.<br />If you soak 4 hours, you might need to boil twenty minutes to get the grains to double their original size.&nbsp; If you soak 24 hours, you only need to boil for a couple of minutes to heat up the grains so they'll flash off the additional moisture as steam, once you drain them.<br />RR"}}